<title>CZECH REPUBLIC: CZECH SPT POSTS '96 CZK 483 MLN LOSS - IAS.</title>
<headline>CZECH SPT POSTS '96 CZK 483 MLN LOSS - IAS.</headline>
<dateline>PRAGUE 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Czech telecommunications company SPT Telecom a.s. said on Tuesday that it posted a 1996 net consolidated loss of 483 million crowns versus a 4.8 billion crown profit in 1995, in international accounting standards.</p>
<p>SPT said that according to Czech accounting standards it posted an unconsolidated 3.5 billion crown net profit in 1996 down from a 4.2 billion crown profit in the previous year. Consolidated results for year ending December 31, 1996 in international accounting standards (in billions of crowns).</p>
<p>			     1996	vs     1995</p>
<p> net result		-0.483 loss	4.829 profit</p>
<p> result before tax     -0.971 loss	7.029 profit</p>
<p> total revenues	  32.483	    26.417</p>
<p> total assets	   106.167	   103.167</p>
<p> fixed assets	    77.851	    59.358</p>
<p> current assets	  28.316	    43.809</p>
<p> total equity	    79.071	    79.534</p>
<p> share capital	   32.209	    32.209</p>
<p> reserves		  46.862	    47.325</p>
<p> liabilities	     27.096	    23.633</p>
<p> total operating costs 18.307	    13.755</p>
<p> EBITD		     14.176	    12.662</p>
<p> depreciation	     6.148	     4.670</p>
<p> EBIT			 8.028	     7.992</p>
<p>impairment and</p>
<p> restructuring charge   8.757	     0.0</p>
<p>contributed services</p>
<p> from telsource	   0.529	     0.100</p>
<p>(CZECH ACCOUNTING RESULTS FOLLOW)</p>
<p>Unconsolidated results for year ending December 31, 1996 in Czech accounting standards (in billions of crowns).</p>
<p>				 1996	vs    1995</p>
<p> pre-tax profit	   4.846		7.056</p>
<p> income tax		 1.390		2.84</p>
<p> profit after tax	 3.456		4.217</p>
<p> revenues		  31.969		n/a</p>
<p> expenses		  24.913		n/a</p>
<p> operating profit	 7.056		8.059</p>
<p>-- Robin Shepherd, Prague Newsroom, 420-2-2423-0003</p>
